121
00:08:54,595 --> 00:08:55,896
See you at work tomorrow.

122
00:08:56,055 --> 00:08:57,325
Stay here.

123
00:08:57,455 --> 00:08:59,325
Don't see me out or come to work.

124
00:09:09,075 --> 00:09:10,636
It's time to give me an answer.

125
00:09:11,075 --> 00:09:13,045
Han Seung Jo's report...

126
00:09:13,046 --> 00:09:15,715
on Haebit Construction's liquidation decision.

127
00:09:16,176 --> 00:09:17,575
Where is it now?

128
00:09:30,256 --> 00:09:32,665
An accounting firm thinks from the creditors' perspective...

129
00:09:32,666 --> 00:09:35,036
and decides whether to keep the company...

130
00:09:35,866 --> 00:09:37,835
that owes money open or shut it down.

131
00:09:39,835 --> 00:09:41,735
Simply put, they weigh out...

132
00:09:42,475 --> 00:09:44,845
which is more profitable, to let the goose live

133
00:09:45,646 --> 00:09:47,844
for the eggs it'll lay in the future,

134
00:09:47,845 --> 00:09:50,646
or to kill it now...

135
00:09:51,116 --> 00:09:52,416
and sell the feathers and meat.

136
00:09:53,215 --> 00:09:55,354
Choosing to keep the goose alive...

137
00:09:55,355 --> 00:09:58,185
and collect the eggs is going concern value.

138
00:09:59,085 --> 00:10:01,824
Killing the goose to sell its feathers and meat...

139
00:10:01,825 --> 00:10:03,156
is liquidation value.

140
00:10:03,855 --> 00:10:06,496
If the liquidation value is higher,

141
00:10:07,095 --> 00:10:08,366
the goose dies,

142
00:10:09,036 --> 00:10:10,396
and the company shuts down.

143
00:10:11,195 --> 00:10:13,366
But if the going concern value is higher,

144
00:10:13,536 --> 00:10:16,305
the goose lives, and so does the company.

145
00:10:17,276 --> 00:10:21,146
In other words, the company's future depends on the accounting firm.

146
00:10:26,246 --> 00:10:28,315
It would've been more profitable to keep Haebit going.

147
00:10:29,685 --> 00:10:31,386
So why did Taeil Accounting...

148
00:10:31,955 --> 00:10:33,725
cut the goose open?

149
00:10:35,555 --> 00:10:36,955
Why did Han Seung Jo...

150
00:10:37,756 --> 00:10:39,296
write up such a report?

151
00:10:53,406 --> 00:10:54,746
You did...

152
00:10:55,646 --> 00:10:56,876
